WorkItem.Description:
I'm trying to add typing to some internal JSON objects I'm creating. Although I'm allowed to type the variables I want, intellisense doesn't seem to be working on them.

For example:
var myObj : MyInterface = 
{
 internalFn: function()
 {
   var test : AnotherInterface = blah;
   test. <== only members within the JSON object come up, not members defined in "AnotherInterface"
 }
};

This is a high priority issue for my company's product as we rely heavily on the ability to create internal constructs within JSON.
